<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Camisiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">CAMISIIDAE</taxonomicName>
Oudemans, 1900
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
Oudemans (1900a) replaced the name 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Nothridae</taxonomicName>
Berlese by 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Camisiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Camisiidae</taxonomicName>
because he considered 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" genus="Nothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Nothrus</taxonomicName>
a synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Camisiidae" genus="Camisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Camisia</taxonomicName>
. Both family-names are in use since Grandjean (1954) placed the two genera in different families.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
It is obvious that Oudemans (1900a) is the author of the family-name 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Camisiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Camisiidae</taxonomicName>
and not Sellnick (1928) as was erroneously mentioned in literature (cf. Radford, 1950, p. 180; Sellnick &amp; Forsslund, 1955; p. 475).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
